						               													<description>Ta Ziemia (This Land) is a family, cooperative board game. It allows players to move back to the year 1979 and participate in the preparations for the first pilgrimage of Polish Pope John Paul II to his homeland plunged in the complicated reality of communism.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The task set for the players in Ta Ziemia is not easy: they must confront the forces of the communist regime, which hinder the organization of the pilgrimage and try to diminish its importance. Players work together to help in preparations for the visit of John Paul II. Acting under pressure of time and the communist regime, players must show cleverness, imagination and the ability to predict opponent's next moves.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Box contains:&amp;#10;- Board&amp;#10;- 44 Renovation cards&amp;#10;- 44 Regime cards&amp;#10;- 10 Central regime cards&amp;#10;- 8 Special city rules cards&amp;#10;- 4 Faction cards&amp;#10;- 16 Citizen pawns&amp;#10;- 1 Time marker&amp;#10;- 15 Influence tiles&amp;#10;- 15 Faith tiles&amp;#10;- 15 Resistance tiles&amp;#10;- 30 Faithful tiles&amp;#10;- 8 Agent tiles&amp;#10;- Instruction&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
